Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
I definitely think this is a good thing.  If students never live on campus, the sense of community greatly decreases.  students must get out of their comfort zone in order to really flourish in college, and i believe that living on campus is a major source of growth in independence.